snippet.textDisplay: I think a big issue about Youtube Rewind that is a big factor of why it will never be the same again is that trends aren't the same anymore. Back in the old days of youtube there would be trends that everyone across the platform would do and viral videos that every viewer would see. But that doesn't happen anymore, viral videos are sparse. Even the videos that are "viral" aren't really viral since its such a huge platform. A lot of the trends that happen on youtube are controversial too, they aren't innocent anymore like the ice bucket challenge or the mannequin challenge. snippet.textDisplay: Hey Mat I have a question. What if we all did it. What if all of the creators and even the viewers came together to make YouTube rewind. Not the company bit it's creators. Like imagine this: if we have a representative of like perhaps every topic from beauty, to gaming, animation, vlogging, and he'll maybe have someone host the entire vid.
